5 Subject: Guardianship; training requirements for guardians
6 Statement of purpose of bill as introduced: This bill proposes to require that
7 special training requirements be established for persons whom a probate court
8 appoints as a guardian for an adult with disabilities.
9 An act relating to training requirements for guardians
10 It is hereby enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Vermont:
11 Sec. 1. 14 V.S.A. § 3071 is amended to read:
12 § 3071. DUTIES OF GUARDIAN
13 (a) The guardian shall maintain close contact with the person under
14 guardianship and encourage maximum self-reliance on the part of the person
15 under guardianship.
16 (b) In addition to the powers vested in the guardian by the court pursuant to
17 section 3069 of this title, the court may order the guardian to assure ensure that
18 the person under guardianship receives those benefits and services to which he
19 or she the person is lawfully entitled and needs to maximize his or her the
