1 (B) The training shall be specific to the constitutional and statutory
2 rights of the person under guardianship, including rights afforded to the person
3 under guardianship by the U.S. and Vermont Constitutions and by section
4 3068a of this title.
5 (C) The training shall include definitions of civil rights and how they
6 apply to adults with disabilities.
7 (2) The proposed guardian shall attend the training program established
8 pursuant to this subsection prior to the commencement of the guardianship and
9 every three years thereafter while the guardianship remains in effect.
10 Sec. 2. EFFECTIVE DATE
11 This act shall take effect on September 1, 2025.
